VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have a 50/90, you can simply just download the installer for my Patreon and then run it to start the installation. If it asks you if you want to enable the CPU offload to reduce the VRM use, you\'re going to press Y and'

[02:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then press enter. And then it\'s going to download and install everything you need to run OV on your own local computer. However, I am sure that for most of you, you will have to use the Runpod installation. And for this, it is'

[02:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually very, very simple. If you don\'t have a Runpod account already, you can click the link in the description down below and create a new account. Then you\'re going to click on pods. And here you\'re going to choose a GPU with at least 32 GB of VRAM. If you want to save'

[02:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'as much money as possible, I highly recommend renting a 5090, for example. But if you really want like the best GPU possible and you don\'t want to compromise on speed, I of course highly recommend renting an RTX Pro 6000. This'

[03:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is going to make the generation much much faster. But for this example, I think that most of you will probably choose a 5090. So here you\'re going to click change template and make sure that you\'re running the runpod pytorch 2.8.0.'

[03:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Then you\'re going to click edit. Here you\'re going to input 100 GB for both container disk and volume disk. And under exposed HTTP port, you\'re going to type comma add 3000. Then you\'re going'

[03:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to click set overrides. Scroll down and then click deploy on demand. Then once it\'s ready, you\'re going to click right here. And then here, if you\'re one of my patrol supporters, the installation will be very, very easy for you because I prepared a special oneclick installer'

