[04:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'well. Okay, so now we can finally have some fun. Now, before we begin, what exactly is OVI and what makes it so special? Well, OVI is an 11 billion parameters model created by Character AI in combination with Yale University. And'

[04:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to make this amazing model, they actually used the 1 2.25 billion parameters model as a base for training, which is a model that I haven\'t really talked about before because to be honest, the quality wasn\'t that great'

[04:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'compared to the 1 2.2 into 28 billion parameters model. But the reason why this model was very very interesting is that it could do text to video and image to video within the same exact model.'

[04:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And all of that inside a 5 billion parameters model and all of that with a resolution of 720p at 24 fps. Something that the 28 billion parameters model was not trained on. Hence probably why they'

[05:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'decided to use that very specific model. However, using this model is a good and a bad thing at the same time. The good news is that since it is an 11 billion parameters model, once we have optimized'

[05:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'versions of that model, a lot of people would be able to run this model very easily on their local computer because 11 billion is definitely less than 14 billion parameters. So even if you had'

[05:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'trouble running 1 2.1, you should be able to run this model instead. So this is good news. Now, one big problem is that this model can only generate 5 seconds of audio and video. So, it is'

[05:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'still fairly limited as of right now. But even then, it\'s still really, really fun to use. The small bad news is that as of right now, as I\'m making this video, there are no optimized versions'

[05:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of that model. You cannot run this on comfy UI, for example. So, the only way you can run this is inside this very specific web UI. But at least it is a very easy to use web UI. So most of you will be able to use it and have fun.'

[06:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Okay. So now that this is done, let\'s have some fun. Okay. So basically here at the very beginning, you can either leave everything blank and it will generate a video from scratch or you can start with an image, which is a thing'

[06:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'what most people will do. So if I\'m click right here and let\'s say I upload an image of this woman taking a selfie, then here in the video prompt, you have to write your prompt in a very specific way. And the way you write your prompt'

[06:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is very simple. So, the way it works is that the first few sentences, you\'re basically going to describe the video. You\'re going to describe the image like a young woman with long dark brown hair, warm brown eyes is shown in a close-up'

[06:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'standing by a sunlight window. She wears a green bal t-shirt smiling brightly at the camera in a casual friendly way. She leans in slightly, her expression playful, and says with energy. And then'

[07:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'when you want to write the dialogue, you\'re going to start the dialogue with this tag right here like S between like these two inferior and superior sign. I don\'t really know how they\'re called,'

[07:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'but basically it start with this tag. And here you\'re going to input your text. So I\'m going to say something like, "Hey guys, it\'s me, your AI overlord." And then you\'re going to end the audio with the tag E. And then you\'re going to continue. For example, say something like, "She tilts her head'

[07:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with a grin." Adding quickly. Then once again, new dialogue. Pretty cool, huh? And then we close the dialogue. And then you can continue. Her smile lingers naturally as if waiting for a reaction. And then you\'re going to end the prompt'

[07:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with the tag old cap and end old cap. And inside the tag, you\'re going to input the characteristics of your character\'s voice. So for example, here I put clear female voice, a bit tone, f street noise outside the window. And if'

[07:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you don\'t know how to write those prompts, you should definitely use shbt for that. I even have a full on text that you can use a full-on prompt that I\'m going to put in my Patreon post and you can just copy and paste inside CH'

[08:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'GPT so that CH GPT understands exactly how the OV prompts are structured so that it can create new ones for you. So the next once you\'ve done that you have the resolution of the video but those resolution does not actually do'

[08:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'anything. If you input an image, it will kind of automatically find the correct resolution depending on the image that you uploaded right here. This is only when you want to generate a video from'

[08:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'scratch. And the maximum resolution is 992x 512. So then you have the video seed. You can input any number you want. Here you have the solver name. And I highly recommend here choose the uler. I feel'

[08:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like this gives better results than the uni one. Then you\'re going to leave everything by default. These are all the best parameters. And here for the video negative prompt, I also found that putting distorted blurry and the foreign'

[09:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'face can also give pretty good results. So you can put that right there. And then you can simply click generate video. And now you wait. And with a 5090, generating a 5-second video takes around 2 and 1/2 minutes. And after a'

[09:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'few minutes, we get something like this. &gt;&gt; Hey guys, it\'s me, your AI overlord. Pretty cool, huh? Yes. Yes, it is. It is pretty cool. I gotta say this is really,'

